        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "get_ipython().run_line_magic('matplotlib', 'inline')\n",
        "from matplotlib import style\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "MG = (17.891, 21.000)\n",
        "RJ = (14.391,17.336)\n",
        "SP = (36.969,46.289)\n",
        "\n",
        "xpos = np.arange(len(SP))\n",
        "xpos\n",
        "\n",
        "style.use('ggplot')\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))\n",
        "barWidth = 0.2\n",
        "plt.bar(xpos,MG, color='royalblue', width = barWidth, label='MG')\n",
        "plt.bar(xpos+0.2,RJ, color='red', width = barWidth, label='RJ')\n",
        "plt.bar(xpos+0.4,SP, color='yellow', width = barWidth, label='SP')\n",
        "plt.xticks(xpos+0.3, ('2000', '2020'))\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Ano')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Quantidade Populacional em Milh√µes')\n",
        "plt.title('Crescimento Populacional')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n"
